features: 63-INCH INDUSTRIAL COMPUTER DESK - Enhance your home office with our sophisticated industrial home office desk featuring a chic brown veins panel design and black frame. Plus, the flexibility to install the drawers on either side of the desk offers customization options to fit your needs.

ALL WITHIN ARM'S REACH - The pull-out keyboard tray provides a designated space for your keyboard, while the printer stand gives your printer a dedicated space. VERSATILE & DURABLE - Crafted from high-quality E1 particleboard and MDF board, this desk with storage boasts exceptional durability, sturdiness, and resilience against scratches and wear. The adjustable leg pads facilitate stable placement of the drawer table even on uneven flooring. Its versatility allows it to function as a computer table, home office desk, study table, writing desk, or executive desk, accommodating different tasks to suit your needs.

CLEAR INSTRUCTIONS & CUSTOMER SERVICE - Assembling our sturdy computer desk with drawer is made easy with our clear and detailed instructions, including numbered parts and all necessary tools for a hassle-free assembly process. Our after-sale team is always ready to provide assistance whenever you need it, ensuring that you have the best experience with our product. Prioritizing our customers' convenience is our top priority.

reviews.reviewText: Great value and enjoying this desk. The area for the printer was too small for my printer. I would have liked to have a file folder drawer.I would buy again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very good quality. Sturdy, nice look, everything fits like I wanted it to. Height is a little too tall I’m short and my chair is at the highest it goes. I’m going to try a pillow. Only reason for 4 stars instead of 5 is that it took me 4 hours to put together and almost the whole thing you have to use an allen key for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Printer will not fit.
reviews.reviewText: We love the desk.although assembly was a little annoying. Pay strict attention to placement of screw holes on the frame and drawer support bars.Smart looking and the price is right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality Desk and features for the price point
reviews.reviewText: To say I shopped a lot of sites and desk configurations for my new desk would be an understatement. I finally settled on this one as it had some key features that I liked with my old desk. The Keyboard drawer is great, but like other reviewers, it is a little too small, so I'm getting a new keyboard in hopes of fixing that issue. Also in my picture I tried to put my printer in the spot I had envisioned for it, but after working at the desk for a bit moved it off as it just didn't fit and took up too much usable space. I love that I'm able to now have 3 monitors, which my old desk didn't support, and it opens up my office space so much more than my old bulkier desk. The drawers are also a key feature that I'm enjoying as well. So many desks are so minimal these days, I wonder where do you keep your "stuff"??? My 15 year old son built the desk for me, and like other reviewers it took a few hours. All in all This is a great purchase and I'm enjoying my new desk!
